wikipedia_page.main: Alicia Pamela Kennedy, Baroness Kennedy of Cradley (born 22 March 1969) is a British Labour politician and member of the House of Lords.

*Alicia Kennedy, Baroness Kennedy of Cradley (born 1969), British politician

link_mentions.page: Roy Kennedy, Baron Kennedy of Southwark
response: His wife is Alicia Kennedy, Baroness Kennedy of Cradley, a former Deputy General Secretary of the Labour Party and now life peer on the Labour benches. She was also elected to Lewisham Council in May 2014, representing the ward of Brockley, in the same Lewisham Deptford Parliamentary Constituency as Lord Kennedy.
